name:
Active mines (1995) for the Northern and Central Appalachian Assessment
coal beds

2000 Resource Assessment of Selected Coal Beds and Zones in the
Northern and Central Appalachian Basin Coal Regions
description:
This dataset is a point coverage of mine locations from the Energy Information
Agency (EIA) database (from coal production Form 7A) that reportedly produce coal
from the 6 coal beds assessed for the northern and central Appalachian Basin coal
regions. Additional beds that are produced are also listed. The correlative bed
names discussed in Chapters F and G of Professional Paper 1625-C were included as
part of the data search from the source information (EIA database).  However, the
coal bed names of this spatial dataset do not necessarily match the geographic
distribution listed by county or coal district discussed in Chapters F and G.
Only minor modifications were made to the original data, which are presented largely
as received from the EIA database search. Coordinates of the mines may not be
the mine workings, but may represent the mine office or other location.

The attributes of the points include up to five coals in order of importance
to production (COAL1 through COAL5). The reported thicknesses of these coals
may also be provided (C1RPTTHK through C5RPTTHK, respectively).
Cover name: mines.shp
